cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.CL 

The paper focuses on cross-modal music video retrieval using audio and video data, which involves multimedia analysis and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel audio-visual embedding algorithm using deep learning techniques, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SD (Sound). The paper also discusses the use of attention-based LSTM models for audio summarization, which is related to natural language processing and falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed model using precision-recall and MAP metrics, which are commonly used in information retrieval and suggest the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
